    "For example, Bidirectional Fig. 1 The original transformer encoder-decoder architecture (Vaswani et al. 2017).",
    "The leftside block represents the encoder, while the right-side block represents the decoder Encoder Representations from Transformers (BERT) uses a stack of 12 encoders in its basic version (Devlin et al. 2018).",
    "The decoder and encoder architectures are very similar, and decoder units (Nx) can also be stacked on each other.",
    "However, the decoder outputs one token at a time since each output token becomes part of the next decoder input (auto-regressive process).",
    "Over this process, the vector of features from the encoder supports the decoder in focusing on the appropriate positions of the input sequence."
